      • authenticateUser

        private boolean authenticateUser​(java.lang.String uname,
                                 char[] pword)
        Authenticates a user based on the username and password provided. Username is stored usind MD5 hashing and the password is stored usind SHA256 hashing. All passwords are handled as char[] since garbage collection for Strings is not immediate, and thus this could be a security issue.
        Parameters:
        uname - String: the username of the user requesting authentication
        pword - char[]: the password, passed as a char array for security reasons [see above]
        Returns:
        boolean: indicating if authentication was successful
